38, 99. insula Cereris. Sicily is one of the many places mentioned as the site of the wanderings of Ceres in search of her daughter, Proserpina, who had been carried off by Pluto. See bk. IV. e. 48. The worship of Ceres (Demeter) was introduced into Sicily by Greek colonists from Corinth, from whom it was borrowed by the Romans.
